data.event: Founded in 1860, it was once a larger community, but it declined for most of the 20th century.

event.title: Today a few commercial buildings remain

data.event: Today a few commercial buildings remain at the intersection of K-4 Highway and 57th Street, but it is mainly a residential area.

event.title: was made a voting precinct of Auburn township, October 1, 1860

data.event: Dover was made a voting precinct of Auburn township, October 1, 1860, and in the fall of 1867, was erected into a township.
